notify.py — Send alerts when new jobs are found
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Called by GitHub Actions after each scrape run.
Only sends a notification if new jobs were found.

Supports three channels — enable whichever you want via GitHub Secrets:

EMAIL (via Gmail SMTP)
NOTIFY_EMAIL_TO      your@email.com
NOTIFY_EMAIL_FROM    your-gmail@gmail.com
NOTIFY_EMAIL_PASS    Gmail App Password (not your real password)
→ gmail.com → Security → App Passwords

DISCORD (via webhook)
NOTIFY_DISCORD_WEBHOOK   https://discord.com/api/webhooks/…
→ Discord server → Edit Channel → Integrations → Webhooks

SLACK (via webhook)
NOTIFY_SLACK_WEBHOOK     https://hooks.slack.com/services/…
→ api.slack.com/apps → Create App → Incoming Webhooks

Set these in: GitHub repo → Settings → Secrets → Actions → New repository secret

USAGE (called by GitHub Actions, but also runnable locally):
python notify.py –new 5 –total 142 –dashboard-url https://you.github.io/jobradar
“””

